social_posts.post_text:
Found myself in Target! Here are a few projects I’ve worked on recently! 🤍 

To be fully transparent sometimes I feel stuck. I’m sure some of you might feel the same way. What I have realized is that even when I don’t see progress there is always progression. If you’re working hard towards your goals you are not in the same place that you were a year ago or two years ago! A year ago all I dreamt of was being booked and busy. Two years ago I dreamt of being in at least one commercial and three years ago I just wanted to get one gig. Remember where you began and don’t give up!

Model tip: In my experience when applying for commercial jobs or print jobs, these are the type of photos that get me booked! Not a lot of makeup and simple. I’m writing this because I wish I knew this when I first started!

You can do anything you want *when you put your mind to it ! 🤍 

So crazy seeing myself all over NYC at CBD Kratom stores! To be honest I have thought about quitting modeling multiple times recently. So seeing this really helped me realize that I have to keep going. Sometimes you might feel discouraged but that’s part of the process. Keep on going even on your worst days!

GRWM 🤍✨ @FashionNova 

#grwm #getdressedwithme #ootd

I am a FIANCÉ!!! 💍🤍 Last night was a dream! What I thought was an early birthday surprise was actually a marriage proposal! I had no clue at all! I am marrying my best friend!! 🥹 Words can’t describe how I feel. The lengths Roy went to get everyone together, plan a dinner, keep this a secret is so beautiful and special to me. I am so happy that I get to spend the rest of my life with my best friend, my soulmate, my partner, my everything! Roy is the best thing that has ever happened to me. I love youuuu sooo much Roy and I am so excited for this next chapter! 🍾💍🤍✨🥰 

Thank you to everyone who came last night! We both really appreciate it! It’s a night we both will never forget! 🥹

This is 25! 🎂

This has by far been the best birthday ever and the best year! I am so grateful for all the blessings coming into my life! Can’t wait to see what this year has in store! ❤️ 

#birthdaygirl

RECAP of the best week of my life! 🌴 

Roy recently surprised me for my bday right after we got engaged! 🎉 We stayed at @occidentalatxcaretdestination and we went to @xcaretpark specifically Xcaret Xplor and Xcaret Mexico. I couldn’t walk much because of my injury but Roy literally carried me all over Mexico so that I could still do the activities. 🥹 It was the best vacation ever! We did Zip lining, ATV’s, swam in a cave, water rafted in a cave, went snorkeling, and so much more! I just loved this vacation so much and wanted to share! 🥺🤍

I surprised Roy with a Spa Day for his bday and we both loved it! I never post this type of content on here but this experience was so amazing I had to share! 🤍

This year has by far been the best year of my life! Today I was reflecting about my year so far and I thought about all the obstacles I had to face this year. Then I thought…wait a minute, there have been so many blessings in my life that have MAJORLY outweighed any obstacle. Roy and I started the new year in the Times Square Ball Drop and we were featured on TV. We both moved out and moved in together into our dream apartment. I went to Mexico twice! Once in April to surprise my mom for her 50th and once in May that Roy surprised me with. Also I got engaged to the love of my life and were planning a wedding!! And my career has been thriving even though I had a foot injury for 4 months and am still recovering. Sometimes we think about the bad things that happen to us instead of realizing all the good! Life is great and I am so grateful. 🤍
